     <div type="poem">
   <pb facs="9"/>
   <pb facs="9"/>
   <head>¶ To the Translatour of <hi>Gerhards Aphorismes.</hi>
   </head>
   <l>DO; Let the Antichristian Clergy keep</l>
   <l>Their Owl-ey'd Laitie pris'ners in the deep</l>
   <l>And horrid shades of everlasting night,</l>
   <l>Whil'st thy clear beams and more illustrious light</l>
   <l>Disperse these clouds of Language, &amp; display</l>
   <l>The close-drawn Curtains of thy new-born day.</l>
   <l>Shine forth, bright Lamp, and chase these shades of night:</l>
   <l>Truth seeks no corners; Errour baulks the light.</l>
   <closer>
      <signed>Ed. Benlowes.</signed>
   </closer>
</div>
